The paper deals with trajectory tracking control of industrial robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of recurrent neural networks (RNNs) for approximating the robot dynamical models suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the uncertain nonlinear dynamics of the robot arm, which indicates a systems and control (cs.SY) aspect. Finally, the use of RNNs for approximating the inverse dynamics suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
